    dc:title "New and little-known sun-moth species from Australia (Lepidoptera, Castniidae)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4322396>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4322398>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4322402>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4322414>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4322400>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4322404> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4322396>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1–2. 1. Synemon sophia, lectotype, male (NHMUK). 2. Synemon parthenoides, lectotype, female (NHMUK)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4322396/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4322398>
    dc:description "FIGURES 3–10. Synemon species adults. Upperside (left), underside (right). 3–6. Synemon sophia, Walpole, Ƌ (3, 4), ♀ (5, 6) (ANIC). 7–10. Synemon cf. leucospila, Ƌ, Martin (7, 8) (ANIC); ♀, Mundaring (9, 10) (ANIC)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4322398/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4322402>
    dc:description "FIGURES 19, 20. Synemon sophia. 19. Male genitalia, a. Unrolled. b. Lateral view, right valva removed. c. Valva. d. Phallus (genitalia slides sl1, sl2) (AMS). 20. Female genitalia. a. Distal part. b. Anterior part. c. Segment 8, ostium, ductus bursae and corpus bursae (genitalia slide sl3) (AMS)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4322402/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4322414>
    dc:description "FIGURES 35–42. Habitat and live specimens of Synemon species. 35. Habitat of Synemon sophia, Walpole. 36. Habitat of Synemon crocea sp. n., Bullsbrook Nature Reserve. 37. Synemon crocea sp. n., larval food-plant Lyginia imberbis, Melaleuca Park Conservation Area. 38–40. Synemon catocaloides, 46 km north-east of Wubin, resting (38), laying eggs at base of its host plant Ecdeiocolea monostachya (39), mating pair (40). 41, 42. Synemon crocea sp. n., Wandena Road, resting posture during cloud cover (41), alert posture in sunshine (42)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4322414/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4322400>
    dc:description "FIGURES 11–18. Synemon species adults. Upperside (left), underside (right). 11–14. Synemon parthenoides, Victoria, Grampians, Ƌ (11, 12), ♀ (13, 14) (CEF). 15–18. Synemon maja, Ƌ, Canna Silo (15, 16) (ANIC); ♀, Howatharra Hill (17, 18) (ANIC)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4322400/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4322404>
    dc:description "FIGURES 21, 22. Synemon species, male genitalia. a. Unrolled. b. Lateral view, right valva removed. c. Valva. d. Phallus 21. Synemon cf. leucospila (genitalia slides 11834, 11836) (ANIC). 22. Synemon parthenoides (genitalia slides 11808, 11809) (ANIC)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4322404/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

